<body>
    <header>
        <h1>Apple Donuts</h1>
        <a href="../../index.html" class="back-button">Back to Main Page</a>
    </header>
    <main>
        <section>
            <h2>Ingredients</h2>
            <ul>
                <li>1 apple of choice</li>
                <li>1 sheet of puff pastry</li>
                <li>⅓ cup sugar of choice</li>
                <li>2 tsp cinnamon</li>
                <li>½ tsp nutmeg</li>
	<li>2 tbsp plant milk</li>
	<li>1 tsp agave</li>
	<li>2 tbsp agave or honey</li>
	<li>1 tsp cinnamon</li>
            </ul>
        </section>
        <section>
            <h2>Instructions</h2>
            <ol>
                <li>Preheat the oven to 400 degrees F and line a baking sheet with parchment.</li>
                <li>Cut an apple into ½ inch rounds, then use a small cookie cutter to create apple rings. You can slice the scraps and use them for something else.</li>
                <li>Combine the sugar, cinnamon, and nutmeg in a bowl or on a plate. Dip your apple rings into the mixture.</li>
                <li>Slice the puff pastry into thin strips, and wrap the dough around the apple rings.</li>
                <li>Combine the plant milk and 1 tsp agave, then brush this mixture onto the donuts. Bake the donuts for 15 minutes or until golden brown on top.</li>
                <li>Combine the agave/honey with the cinnamon and drizzle over the donuts.</li>
            </ol>
        </section>
    </main>
</body>
